objects.name: Mule Libra
objects.description: Mule Libra, also known as Cobalt Gang, is a financially motivated threat group that has primarily targeted financial institutions. The group has conducted intrusions to steal money via targeting ATM systems, card processing, payment systems and SWIFT systems. Mule Libra has mainly targeted banks in Eastern Europe, Central Asia, and Southeast Asia. One of the alleged leaders was arrested in Spain in early 2018, but the group still appears to be active. The group has been known to target organizations in order to use their access to then compromise additional victims. Reporting indicates there may be links between Mule Libra and both the malware Carbanak and the group Carbanak.

objects.name: Campaign 1 - [Playbook] Mule Libra
objects.description:
During October 2018, Unit 42 has been investigating ongoing Mule Libra campaigns, as well as leveraging the latest information publicly reported in research reports, such as the ones described by Talos or Morphisec, to help discover and tie new infrastructure to this attack group.

As a result, Unit 42 was able to identify both the use of a common macro builder as well as specific document metadata which have allowed us to track and cluster new activity and infrastructure associated with Mule Libra
